Pizza Sales Data Analysis Dashboard
Project Overview
This project provides an in-depth analysis of pizza sales using Power BI, SQL, and Microsoft Excel. The goal was to generate insightful Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) and visualize trends and patterns to support data-driven decision-making.

Tech Stack Used
Power BI: For data visualization and dashboard creation.
SQL: For querying and managing the dataset.
Microsoft Excel: For data preprocessing and cleaning.
Features
Interactive Dashboard: The Power BI dashboard is equipped with dynamic visuals that allow users to filter data by various dimensions, such as time, pizza type, and store location.
KPIs: Key metrics such as total revenue, average order value, and sales growth rate are prominently displayed for quick insights.
Trend Analysis: Visualizations reveal patterns over time, such as seasonal trends, top-selling pizzas, and customer preferences.
Sales Performance by Location: Compare sales across different store locations to identify high-performing regions.
Insights Delivered
Identified top-selling pizza categories and individual pizzas.
Revealed seasonal sales trends, helping to inform inventory management and marketing strategies.
Pinpointed peak sales periods and high-performing store locations.
Visualizations
Bar Charts: Show breakdowns of sales by pizza type and region.
Line Graphs: Track monthly revenue and sales growth.
KPIs: Displayed prominently on the dashboard for quick reference.
How to Run the Project
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/pizza-sales-dashboard.git
Open the Power BI file Pizza_Sales_Dashboard.pbix.
Use Power BI to explore the interactive dashboard.
Future Improvements
Incorporating customer demographics to gain deeper insights.
Adding predictive analytics to forecast future sales trends.
